parameters: \pop[3]What's gonna happen next in our R&R Campaign?
\pop[4]That's a GM secret, thank you very much.
\pop[3]Don't tell me you already have it planned.
\pop[3]A good GM lets their players build the story.
You roll with what they give you. It's basically improv.
Like; what if I betrayed Dante and \c[10]killed him\c[0]?
Any story arcs you had planned would be totally shot.
You have to be ready for anything, Taylor.
\pop[4]For some reason, I don't believe you.
You're a novelist. There's no \c[14]way\c[0] you can wing your stories.
You can try your best to guide us down your chosen path.
But at the end of the day, we're still able to forge our own.
We have \c[17]Komorebi\c[0], but a lot of us defy our visions.
\pop[4]I always thought that sounded so... ominous.
\pop[3]Not really. I think it's more of an optimism thing.
One person can change the world for everybody.
\pop[4]Makes sense that \c[14]you'd\c[0] see it that way.
I wonder if your R&R character is similar, though...
\pop[3]Not really. He thinks a lot smaller than me.
More than anything, he wants to know the truth about his parents.
\pop[3]That's basically it. I was an information broker, right?
I figure that was \c[14]one\c[0] piece of information I always wanted.
Why my parents abandoned me in Mazeo as a child.
I think I can weave it into the story.
Right now, I feel like more of an archetype.
\pop[3]I wouldn't mind having a cool story, too.
\pop[4]I think I want to use my influence, and shape Mazeo.
I'm already the elder of Valinorth, right?
\pop[4]Well, I think my parents were killed in Mazeo.
It makes me want to change the nation; make it safer.
That way, nobody else has to go through what I did.
\pop[3]What about mine? I was in charge of The Rebellion, right?
\pop[3]Well, I like to think that I lost my mentor figure.
He was the leader before me, and I had to fill his shoes.
But I'm inexperienced, and struggle with adapting.
\pop[3]Makes sense. You're more of a right-hand man.
\pop[3]Can I go next? I got a good one.
\pop[3]I used to work for the enemies. I know them better than anyone else.
Because of that, I was able to help tip the war in our favor.
But not everyone trusts me, and doubt lingers in the air.
\pop[4]Once a traitor, always a traitor, right?
I wonder what Delta's backstory would be.
\pop[3]We should ask them after their appointment.
If we get to choose our history, then so should they.
How am I supposed to balance all these threads?
\pop[3]Just go with the flow, like you do with your chat.
You may be streaming, but they're in control.
You're gonna be fine, Taylor. Don't worry.
\pop[4]I'll try. But if I need help, I'll ask.
\pop[3]Of course. We're all in this together, now.
\pop[3]Fighting against fate, both on and off the board.
Kinda cool how our goals are similar, no matter what lives we live.
